  "text": "whether mutations in the ar/R-motif of AQP3 affect its ability to discriminate between glycerol and urea, we constructed several point mutants and measured glycerol and urea permeability. Substitution of the tyrosine residue in position 3 for alanine (Y212A) conferred measurable urea permeability, whilst concomitantly reducing glycerol Representative calcein fluorescence timeseries from HEK293 cells transfected with AQP4 H201A or H201G and exposed to iso-osmotic solutions containing 150 mM of urea or glycerol. (E) Cell swelling rate constants from (A) above normalized to surface expression and then normalized to AQP3 glycerol permeability. This gives a relative single channel permeability in units in which AQP3 glycerol permeability is 1. (F) Normalized permeabilities for the analogous mutants of AQP1 for comparison. Panels A, B, D and F are adapted from P. Kitchen PhD thesis [CITATION_1] .",
